<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="550" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1436,152,395]" pageId="27" pageNumber="550">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,296,323]" pageId="27" pageNumber="550">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body robust; prothorax with lateral tubercles placed centrally; pronotum with three tubercles; elytra without centrobasal crest or longitudinal carina; elytra with setose granules all over the surface; basal metatarsomere as long as next two together. Number of species currently included: 5.
</paragraph>
